srcinfo.srccontr:
ESRI, Admin,
The sub Country Administrative Units 1998 GeoDataset represents a small-scale political map of the world. The data are generalized and were designed for display at scales to about 1:10,000,000. The data were generalized from ESRI's ArcWorld Supplement Map data. Country codes are from U.S. Federal Information Processing Standards (FIPS) version 10-4. Please note Thanks to ESRI for use of the Orginal Administration Boundaries. "Administrative boundary files are the intellectual property of ESRI and its licensors and are using herein with permission. © 1992-1997 ESRI, GMI. All Rights Reserved."

citeinfo.title: World Data Bank (WDB) II Binary files:
citeinfo.othercit: The World Data Bank II outline files are digitized from navigational charts to a working scale of approximately 1:3 Million, and represent the "state of the art" in the mid 1970s. There are three files composing the WDB-II set on this CD-ROM: coastlines, rivers and lakes, and political boundaries (the last becoming increasingly obsolete!). Some of the details contained in the original WDB files, such as "order" of the elements (as related to size and importance of islands or lakes) have been left out of these versions -- the full and official WDB is available from the National Technical Information Service, Springfield, VA.

procstep.procdesc: Electron version of the publication supplied in pdf format (tdwg geo2b.pdf)
Text for each level copies and parsed into MSaccess (TDWG2.mdb)

Level 4 table, odbc to Arcview 3.2 and joined first on country name in admin 98, if hit the level 4 code was added to the admin98.dbf, then joined on administration boundary name. Missed regions were added to the dbf file.
Some areas (ie island groups) exploded to break them from the group, groups where then classifed correctly.
Some boundary, split by adding boundary line accross major polygon. Two resultant polygons reclassifed.
Addition polygons added from WVS 1:3 Million (from lines to polygons) from missed islands.
Tables from ArcView (dbf) imported into MSacess and compare to tables from the new standard. Any anomalise where corrected (master.shp)
Master.shp file was merged on the various levels (1-4) and shape files saved with text attriubtions (level1, level2, level3, level4)
Addition of Kew Regions to master dataset
EHM-DJ - Darjiling - four small islands south of West Bengal were attached to the Darjiling layer - split and rename to west Bengal.

dataqual.logic: Data is derived most from world admin dataset from ESRI (1998), with additions form districts/countries that have changes and the addition of islands from WVS 1:3,000,000. Scale of dataset would be 1:5,000,000 to 1:3,000,000
dataqual.complete: This is the first release of this dataset. there is likely to be a few mistakes
